cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.LG. 

This paper involves natural language processing and social network analysis, which are both interdisciplinary fields that can fall under multiple sub-categories. However, the focus on social networks and the use of graph embedding methods suggest that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are the most likely sub-categories. The use of natural language processing techniques also suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a possible sub-category. The analysis of temporal embeddings and the comparison of user roles over time may also fall under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
